So, if `error` is in `clip_info`, then it automatically is invalid. This is why I check for `error` in `clip_info` before anything else. Because if `error` is in `clip_info`, there will never be format information.

You say that
> even if clip_info exist, it's possibe that there is no format there(empty contentUrl* values).

But if `clip_info` exists (i.e. `parsed['clips'][video_id]` exists) and `parsed['clips'][video_id]['error']` exists, then there will not be a `contentUrl` value.

Are you saying that I must check if at least one format is returned? E.g. in the case when there is `clip_info`, no `clip_info['error']` and no `clip_info['contentUrl']`? If so, surely that will be covered in the case when there are no formats retrieved? 
