Recommend switch the if-statement to avoid an else block:
```c
if (..whatever is wrong) {
  i++;
  goto err;
}
```

General recommendation is to keep the level of indent blocks down and typically only do indents for the error cases, e.g.:
```c
if (some_error) {
  handle_it..
  and stuff;
}

good_things();

if (some other_error)
  goto err;

more good things();

```

